menu "NucleoOS ANIMA"

    config NUCLEO_ANIMA_BENCH
        bool "Run the ANIMA Phase 0 benchmark at boot"
        default n
        help
            Run nucleo_anima_benchmark() once during boot and log the three numbers
            (int8 MAC throughput, Hamming/popcount rate, SD read MB/s) over the serial
            monitor. Off by default so normal boot is unchanged. See docs/anima.md §8.

    config NUCLEO_ANIMA_HDC_SELFTEST
        bool "Run the ANIMA HDC/KGE reasoning self-test at boot"
        default n
        help
            Run nucleo_anima_hdc_selftest() once during boot: the hyperdimensional
            reasoning core (semantic atoms, key->value recall, deduction by rotation,
            resonance-coherence honesty) proven on real silicon, plus popcount
            throughput. Logs PASS/FAIL over the serial monitor. Off by default -> this
            file compiles to a no-op stub and the normal firmware is byte-for-byte
            unchanged (zero RAM/flash cost). Reference impl: tools/anima/hdc.mjs + kge.mjs.

endmenu
